text.tspan: Usually a List or Array, but also
where map( f(a->b), Wrapped<a>) yields Wrapped<b>
with identity law map id xs = xs
and composition law map g (map f xs) = map (g <<< f) xs
Composition: pure (<<<) <*> f <*> g <*> h = f <*> (g <*> h)
Associative composition: (<<<) <$> f <*> g <*> h = f <*> (g <*> h)
Left Identity: pure x >>= f = f x
Associativity: (x >>= f) >>= g = x >>= (\k -> f k >>= g)
Apply Superclass: apply f x = f >>= \f’ -> map f’ x
